# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#  AI assistant — OPTIONAL, FREE
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# The AI works out of the box using a built-in local analysis engine.
# To power it with a REAL LLM, copy this file to ".env.local" and set ONE of:
#
# ── Option 1: Groq (recommended — FREE, no credit card) ──
#   Get a key in ~60s at: https://console.groq.com/keys
# GROQ_API_KEY=gsk_your_key_here
# GROQ_MODEL=llama-3.3-70b-versatile
#
# ── Option 2: any OpenAI-compatible API (OpenAI, OpenRouter, DeepSeek…) ──
# OPENAI_API_KEY=sk_your_key_here
# OPENAI_BASE_URL=https://api.openai.com/v1
# OPENAI_MODEL=gpt-4o-mini
#
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#  Telegram bot — OPTIONAL, FREE (best picks pushed to your chat)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 1. In Telegram, open @BotFather → /newbot → copy the token.
# 2. Open your new bot and press START (send any message once).
# 3. Set the token below — chat id is auto-detected from your /start.
# TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN=123456789:AA...your_token...
# TELEGRAM_CHAT_ID=            # optional — auto-detected if empty

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#  24/7 server-side scan — OPTIONAL (works after deploy)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# When set, /api/cron/scan requires ?key=<this> (or Vercel Cron's auth header).
# A scheduler (Vercel Cron / cron-job.org) hits it to push the best picks to
# Telegram even when the site is closed. Pick any long random string.
# CRON_SECRET=change_me_to_a_long_random_string

# After editing, restart:  npm run dev
# Keys are read server-side only and never sent to the browser.
